{
  "texts": [
    "Another important factor to think about is how the system plans to get the necessary data.",
    "Yu et al. [39] developed a dataset called visual madlibs for Visual Question Answering (VQA), which calls for a system that can answer both multiple-choice and complete the blank questions.An organized framework for visual inquiry is provided by visual madlibs.",
    "This assists the system in identifying the best strategy, whether attribute prediction for inquiries about an object's attributes (type 6) or saliency detection for answering intriguing questions about the picture (type 3).",
    "Using joint-embeddings or deep-learning algorithms is a straightforward and successful strategy, according to the dataset developers.",
    "Including a classification of Visual Questions (VQ), Visual7w is an additional Visual Question Answering (VQA) dataset."
  ]
}